reviews.text: The food here is fantastic and delicious. The appetizers are all tasty and will serve as a great start to your meal. There are MANY options, however let it be known, they do duck very well as well as spicy dishes. The entrees are portioned well as it will be a pleasing serving size. There is a limited beer list, but isnt a dry restaurant, so you might find a wine/beer you'd like. The atmosphere is quiet and homely feeling, but will still leave more than happy.

I absolutely love this place! The setting is cute and quaint, the staff are very friendly, the place is clean, and the food is delicious! I recently had the seafood basil lomein. Everything was cooked to perfection. The sauce was very flavorful and had just the right amount of kick. The price is slightly higher than other restaurants that I've been to, but the portion is very generous and the ingredients are very high quality. I also tried the Thai custard sticky rice dessert which was a very good way to end the meal. The custard was soft and a little sweet, but not sickly sweet which was nice. I also recommend getting the Thai iced tea, this is probably the best one that I've ever had.
I will definitely be coming back here soon!

This is a decent Thai restaurant. The staff is a bit aloof, but professional enough. The food is good and there's a lot of variety.

Entrees will run from $11-18.

Parking is pretty tight. There's a large lot, but it is often very crowded.
The owner seem to prefer other races over Asian despite her being Thai herself. I love the food and everything, but I never really got a smile or thank you from those ladies. I feel discriminated.
The appetizer platter is phenomenal.  Pad Thai is delicious. Very fair pricing. Staff is attentive but not in your face. We've been here before, and will be back.
